{"type":"message","id":"27f0ec60","parentId":"8bb13a21","timestamp":"2026-04-08T07:27:02.101Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"HALEI has been asking multiple questions and I haven't responded to them yet. Let me address them now:\n\n1. Is configuring OpenViking redundant when upgrading to this version?\n2. Any suggestions on the existing storage architecture?\n3. Should `~/.openclaw/openviking.env` be deleted?\n4. Did I receive their messages?\n\nThe messages started at 15:10 and now it's 15:25 - I haven't replied to any of these. Let me respond to all their questions now.\n\nFor the OpenViking question - based on the doctor output, OpenViking is registered as a context engine with `before_prompt_build=auto-recall, afterTurn=auto-capture, assemble=archive+active`. It's working alongside memory-lancedb. The memory search doctor output says \"No active memory plugin is registered for the current config\" - which might suggest that neither memory-core nor OpenViking's memory is properly configured as the active memory plugin. But OpenViking IS registered as a context engine.\n \nLooking more carefully at the setup, OpenViking is functioning as the context brain while LanceDB persists the memory store, so they're designed to work together rather than being redundant. Whether both are necessary depends on what you're optimizing for - if you want semantic memory search and recall, OpenViking with LanceDB is the intended path in this version, whereas older setups relied on memory-core. The `openviking.env` file is part of this configuration and shouldn't be removed unless you're switching away from this setup entirely.","thinkingSignature":"b785b4e7511bab556e1405ddcb1d3baca1813217cc0709856597cad07f43b8c9"},{"type":"text","text":"抱歉，连续几条消息都没及时回复！逐条回答：\n\n**1. OpenViking 配置是否多余？**\n不是多余。doctor 输出显示 OpenViking 已作为 context-engine 正常注册：\n- `before_prompt_build=auto-recall` — 每次回复前召回相关记忆\n- `afterTurn=auto-capture` — 每次对话后自动捕捉内容存档\n- `assemble=archive+active` — 组装时合并归档+活跃上下文\n\n它和 LanceDB 是配套的：OpenViking 负责**检索/召回策略**，LanceDB 负责**向量存储**。4.8 版本推荐这套架构。\n\n**2. 当前存储架构建议**\n现有结构清晰合理：\n- Session 历史用 JSONL（够用，5.7MB）\n- 记忆用 LanceDB 向量库（76KB，轻量）\n- 工作区/扩展分离\n\n如果后续记忆数据量上来（几千条以上）， LanceDB 的向量检索优势会明显。暂时没毛病。\n\n**3. `openviking.env` 要删除吗？**\n先别删。查看一下里面的内容，如果是 OpenViking 的 API key 或配置，删除后 OpenViking context-engine 会失效。如果里面只是空的或默认内容，可以删。但保险起见先让我看一眼内容再说。\n\n要不要我查一下这个文件？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35,"output":591,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":24582,"totalTokens":25208,"cost":{"input":0.0000105,"output":0.0007092,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.00921825,"total":0.009937950000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775633199353,"responseId":"0625362fb648b6d14d6937f59021abe8"}}
