{"type":"message","id":"bb45ce6b","parentId":"e21c19d7","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:16:14.541Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-08 18:15:08 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b5256e471ecb8c4dafc88f002915]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5256e471ecb8c4dafc88f002915\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-04-08 18:15 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n不是说使用了这两个数据库后，token的使用都会降低吗"}],"timestamp":1775643374536}}
{"type":"message","id":"04fdda7f","parentId":"bb45ce6b","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:16:34.730Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking whether using LanceDB + OpenViking would reduce token usage. Let me think about this.\n\nThe idea behind vector memory systems like OpenViking + LanceDB is:\n- They use semantic search to recall relevant memories/context\n- This allows the AI to work with a smaller active context (because only relevant memories are retrieved)\n- So yes, in theory, token usage should be lower because you're not stuffing the entire conversation history into every prompt\n\nHowever, the user's experience shows:\n1. OpenViking needs to call MiniMax embedding API to create vectors for recall - this costs embedding tokens\n2. The user is on coding plan with limited embedding quota\n3. The recall is failing because of \"insufficient balance\"\n\n\n4. So while the architecture is designed to reduce tokens by retrieving only relevant memories, the embedding calls themselves consume quota, and the user's plan apparently doesn't have enough to support this approach\n\nThe trade-off is clear: you're swapping embedding API calls for fewer main model tokens, but if your plan's embedding quota is too small, the system breaks down before you can realize those savings. The real issue is that LanceDB and OpenViking are both trying to use the same memory tools simultaneously, causing a conflict. While OpenViking's semantic retrieval could theoretically reduce token usage by selectively recalling only relevant memories rather than feeding entire conversation histories, this benefit only materializes if you have sufficient embedding quota—which the user currently lacks.","thinkingSignature":"8f223ce6a802d6dbcf220a0893744028f2ea4b215e20fa88ccaa161d037952e8"},{"type":"text","text":"理论上是对的，但有个前提条件：\n\n**OpenViking + LanceDB 节省 token 的逻辑：**\n- 不用每次都把完整对话历史塞进 context\n- 召回时只拉取语义相关的记忆片段\n- 主模型的输入 token 减少 → 省钱\n\n**但你当前的实际情况：**\n- OpenViking 每次召回都要调用 MiniMax embedding → **embedding token 消耗**\n- 你的 coding plan embedding 额度不够 → embedding 一直失败\n- 失败后记忆召回完全失效，等于系统降级运作\n\n**结论：** 这套架构本身是省 token 的设计，但前提是 embedding 服务要能正常工作。如果你的 embedding 额度长期不足，OpenViking 就形同虚设，反而是负担。\n\ncoding plan 的 embedding 额度具体是多少？如果额度很少（比如 <1M tokens/月），长期撑不住 OpenViking 的消耗。如果额度够用，充值后就能进入正向循环。\n\n你的 coding plan 额度是多少？我帮你估算一下够不够用。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35,"output":502,"cacheRead":36057,"cacheWrite":712,"totalTokens":37306,"cost":{"input":0.0000105,"output":0.0006024,"cacheRead":0.0021634199999999997,"cacheWrite":0.000267,"total":0.0030433199999999995}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775643374541,"responseId":"06255deef760525f0407f488332631f2"}}
