{"type":"message","id":"63b39f6e","parentId":"d79bf642","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:25:16.712Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-08 18:24:10 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b5256826e5cb8c2c46868a020aa4]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5256826e5cb8c2c46868a020aa4\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-04-08 18:24 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n用一个token不就行了。为啥还要单独embedding 呢"}],"timestamp":1775643916705}}
{"type":"message","id":"0bd9689c","parentId":"63b39f6e","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:25:41.672Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good question from HALEI. They're asking: why do we need separate embedding tokens at all, why not just use the main model's tokens for everything?\n\nThis is a good question. Let me explain the difference:\n\n1. **Main model tokens (MiniMax M2)** - Used for reasoning/generating responses. These are expensive.\n\n2. **Embedding tokens** - Used specifically to convert text into vector representations for semantic search. These are a different type of token, often cheaper.\n\nThe reason you need separate embedding is:\n- The embedding model is specifically trained to convert text → vectors (numerical representations of meaning)\n- This is different from the reasoning model (MiniMax M2) which generates text\n- The embedding model is typically a separate, specialized model\n\n\n- LanceDB and OpenViking rely on these vector representations to quickly retrieve relevant memories, whereas without embeddings they'd need to fall back to keyword matching or loading all historical context directly into the main model, which would be much more expensive.\n\nSo the core difference is that OpenViking uses semantic vector search to selectively retrieve only the most relevant memories, keeping your main model context lean and focused. Without embeddings, you'd either pay to stuff all history into the model or sacrifice the precision of retrieval. The reason LanceDB and OpenViking can't just use the main model for everything is that they're fundamentally different operations—semantic vector search requires a specialized embedding model to convert text into numerical vectors for efficient similarity matching, whereas text generation needs a full reasoning model like MiniMax M2. Embedding models are typically cheaper and faster for this specific task, so the architecture separates concerns: embeddings handle retrieval and context assembly, while the main model handles generation.","thinkingSignature":"a65d8209a2201ad4a78e3becdcd5bf25dac26704c8f3ac2ecee5f7345462c203"},{"type":"text","text":"问得好，说清楚这个逻辑：\n\n**Embedding 和主模型（生成）的区别：**\n\n| | Embedding 模型 | 主模型（MiniMax M2） |\n|---|---|---|\n| 做什么 | 文本 → 向量（数字列表） | 文本 → 文本（生成回复） |\n| 用途 | 语义搜索、相似度匹配 | 推理、生成回答 |\n| 特点 | 专用于向量化，快且便宜 | 通用的推理引擎，贵 |\n\n**为什么不能省掉 embedding：**\n\n举个具体例子——我要回答你\"我的飞书配置是什么\"这个问题：\n\n1. **没有 embedding**：我需要把整个历史对话塞给主模型，让它自己去找相关内容 → 每次都要带几百条历史 → **主模型 token 爆炸**\n\n2. **有 embedding**：你的问题先转成向量 → 在 LanceDB 里0.1秒找到相关内容 → 只把最相关的3-5条记忆放进 context → **主模型 token 大幅减少**\n\n**OpenViking 的核心逻辑：**\n```\n你提问 → Embedding 转换 → 向量搜索（快、准） → 只召回相关记忆 → 塞给主模型\n```\n\n主模型不知道自己记住了什么，它只能看到我喂给它的上下文。Embedding 就是那个\"快速定位\"记忆的索引系统。\n\n所以 embedding 不是额外开销，而是**降低主模型 token 消耗的手段**。coding plan 的 embedding 额度应该够用，关键是要充足。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35,"output":642,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":37259,"totalTokens":37936,"cost":{"input":0.0000105,"output":0.0007704,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.013972125,"total":0.014753025}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775643916712,"responseId":"0625600d265997470799fbf4cf19f572"}}
