{"type":"message","id":"06a310bb","parentId":"2d0700d2","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:33:49.221Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-08 18:32:41 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b5256a25ce510c4cdb58bcc48366]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5256a25ce510c4cdb58bcc48366\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-04-08 18:32 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n意思是大模型中还要有专门针对 embedding 额度和功能？  minimax2.7 不也是多模态的吗"}],"timestamp":1775644429215}}
{"type":"message","id":"0227b71f","parentId":"06a310bb","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:34:12.206Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking a good technical question - they're confused about why MiniMax (which is a multimodal model) can't do embedding directly. They're right to be confused because some models like GPT-4 can handle both embedding and generation.\n\nLet me clarify:\n\n1. MiniMax M2/M2.7 are **text generation models** - they take text in, generate text out. They're not specialized embedding models.\n\n2. While they might have some internal text understanding, the **embedding** step (converting text to a vector) is a specific mathematical process (like word2vec, BERT embeddings, etc.) that requires a different type of model architecture.\n\n\n3. The API for MiniMax likely has separate endpoints - one for chat/completion and another for embeddings, and the coding plan probably limits access to one or both of these.\n\n4. Most modern AI systems separate these concerns architecturally: embedding models are optimized for similarity searches (fast vector ops), while generation models handle reasoning and response creation. Even though OpenAI's newer models can do both, the distinction remains useful in production systems.\n\n5. MiniMax likely offers separate APIs with independent rate limits - the chat completion quota and embedding quota are managed separately, so the user might have exhausted one while the other remains available. The `insufficient balance` error suggests the embedding endpoint specifically is what's blocked, not the generation side.\n\nI should acknowledge their intuition is sound - some models do support both - but explain why most providers including MiniMax keep them separate, and suggest they check which specific API key or quota is actually exhausted.","thinkingSignature":"7b6a9887ac19305ae4169c7b9f43d5f34f754db95e662b4e283a5c4289e9c0c2"},{"type":"text","text":"问得对，混淆在这里很常见。\n\n**MiniMax M2/M2.7 是生成模型，不是 embedding 模型。**\n\n虽然都是\"大模型\"，但做的事完全不同：\n\n- **生成模型（MiniMax M2/M2.7）** — 推理、写作、对话。架构是 Decoder-only Transformer。\n- **Embedding 模型** — 把文本转成向量。架构通常是 BERT 系列或者专门的 embedding-oriented 模型。\n\n可以理解成：一个是厨师（炒菜），一个是仓库管理员（分类检索）。两个工种虽然都是 AI，但技能树不同。\n\n**那 MiniMax 的 embedding 额度从哪来？**\n\nMiniMax 开放了单独的 Embedding API 端点，和主模型 API 是分开的计费/限额体系。coding plan 应该是给了两部分额度：\n\n```\nChat Completion 额度（主模型）→ 一直够用\nEmbedding 额度 → 很快耗尽（因为你一直在对话，embedding 每次都调用）\n```\n\n你今天对话了多久？embedding 会为**每条消息**都生成向量存进 LanceDB，日积月累消耗很快。\n\n**最实际的解法：**\n去 MiniMax 控制台看一下 embedding 额度的剩余量，如果确实快没了，充值是最快的解决办法。或者换一个 embedding provider（比如 Jina AI 有免费额度）接入 OpenViking。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35,"output":590,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":37853,"totalTokens":38478,"cost":{"input":0.0000105,"output":0.000708,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.014194875000000001,"total":0.014913375000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775644429222,"responseId":"0625620d4d53129aa6a02f3107383d22"}}
