{"type":"message","id":"f84e7904","parentId":"280c42a0","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:35:42.045Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-08 18:34:36 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b5256bd7648b4c11bbd17bd31caa]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5256bd7648b4c11bbd17bd31caa\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-04-08 18:34 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\n我现在用的是这个模型，\n600次模型调用 / 5小时\n支持最新 MiniMax M2.7，正常约50TPS，低峰时段100TPS\n\n约支持1个OpenClaw agent\n\n支持主流的编程工具，并持续扩展中\n\n支持图像理解、联网搜索 MCP\n\n每周可使用额度为「每5 小时额度」的 10 倍"}],"timestamp":1775644542040}}
{"type":"message","id":"04746b08","parentId":"f84e7904","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:36:06.597Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me their current plan details:\n- 600 model calls per 5 hours\n- MiniMax M2.7 support\n- ~50TPS normal, 100TPS low peak\n- ~1 OpenClaw agent\n- Image understanding, web search, MCP\n- 10x the 5-hour limit per week = 6000 calls/week\n\nThis seems like a coding plan for OpenClaw, not a MiniMax API plan directly. The 600 calls/5 hours would be the main model (Chat Completion) calls, not embedding calls.\n\nThe issue is that the embedding calls are separate from the main model calls, and the embedding might be using a different API or额度 that isn't explicitly mentioned here.\n\n\nLooking at the numbers more carefully, 600 calls every 5 hours breaks down to just 2 calls per minute, which isn't much breathing room. The embedding failures showing \"insufficient balance\" point to a separate issue though—these might be handled through a different service or the embedding calls are being counted against a different quota than the main model calls.\n\nThe real problem is that the user has two separate systems in play: the MiniMax API for embeddings (which is depleted) and this OpenClaw plan (which has its own 600 call limit). These are functioning independently, so resolving the embedding issue would require addressing the MiniMax quota separately from the OpenClaw plan limits.\n\nThe \"insufficient balance\" error on embeddings could stem from either an exhausted MiniMax account or possibly a configuration issue in the OpenViking setup where it's pointing to the wrong API endpoint. I should clarify whether the user has a direct MiniMax API account or if everything is being routed through OpenClaw's platform.","thinkingSignature":"f9789782bb9cedbe2640801e388d5c23a373abc05c9a5961f61b0887439a08c4"},{"type":"text","text":"这个 OpenClaw plan 的 600次/5小时 是**主模型（Chat Completion）的调用限额**，不是 embedding 限额。\n\nembedding 报错说\"insufficient balance\"，说明你的 MiniMax API 账户本身 embedding 额度已经耗尽，跟这个 plan 是两套账本：\n\n```\nOpenClaw plan（主模型调用）→ 600次/5小时 ← 这个是你的 plan 额度\nMiniMax API（embedding）→ 余额不足 ← 这是 MiniMax 开发者账户的额度\n```\n\n你在 MiniMax 开放平台有账户吗？如果有，登录控制台能看到 embedding 额度的使用情况。\n\n**两个问题需要分开解决：**\n\n1. **MiniMax embedding 额度** — 去 miniMax 开放平台充值，这是让记忆功能工作的前提\n2. **OpenClaw plan 600次/5小时** — 这个是主模型对话限额，跟 embedding 是两码事\n\n简单说：你的 OpenClaw plan 保证主模型能跑，但 OpenViking 的向量功能依赖 MiniMax 开发者账户那边的 embedding 额度，那边空了。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35,"output":579,"cacheRead":37906,"cacheWrite":563,"totalTokens":39083,"cost":{"input":0.0000105,"output":0.0006948,"cacheRead":0.00227436,"cacheWrite":0.000211125,"total":0.003190785}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775644542045,"responseId":"0625627ead2cea48a1ebead5ed48ac85"}}
