{"type":"message","id":"358ad6e3","parentId":"01e0bb67","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:37:58.905Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the structure. The product-selector has its own models.json with only OpenRouter. I need to add a Gemini provider to the product-selector's models.json.\n\nThe user wants to add Gemini API and configure it for the product-selector agent. However, I need to note something important:\n\nThe user said \"如果可以给 Embedding用\" (if it can be used for Embedding). \n\nBut wait - Gemini API for embedding is a different API endpoint. The OpenClaw models.json config here is for **chat/completion models**, not for **embedding models**. These are two different things:\n- Chat models: `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/gemini-pro:generateContent`\n\n\n- Embedding models: `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/embedding-001:embedContent`\n\nSo the models.json can add a Gemini chat provider, but whether OpenViking can actually USE Gemini for embedding depends on OpenViking's own configuration. OpenViking might only support certain embedding providers.\n\nBut actually, the user might be confused. Let me re-read their message: \"帮我把这个gemini的api 先配置到大模型列表里面，我先给选品agent配置上，我测试一下，如果可以给 Embedding用\" - They're asking me to add the Gemini API to the large model list and configure it for the product-selector agent so they can test if it works for embedding.\n\nI should add Gemini to product-selector's models.json, but I need to clarify that models.json is for chat/completion models while embedding is a separate system. I'll use `google/gemini-pro` or `google/gemini-2.0-flash` as the model ID with the standard Google AI API endpoint. However, there's a bigger issue here - the current OpenViking is failing because MiniMax embedding is out of balance, not because of the chat model itself.\n\nAdding Gemini as a chat provider won't solve the embedding issue unless OpenViking specifically supports Gemini embeddings, which I'm uncertain about. Let me just proceed with configuring Gemini in the models.json for the chat model and clarify this distinction with the user. I should probably ask for their Gemini API key since I don't have it stored in the workspace TOOLS.md or credentials file.","thinkingSignature":"053d55720bf2ec473df787683d209d7ca095f722f016781682813abd9f861a01"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了。product-selector 有自己的 models.json，只有 OpenRouter。\n\n但有个关键点要先说清楚：\n\n**models.json 是配置 Chat/Completion 模型的**，而 embedding 是另外一套系统。\n\n- **Chat 模型** — 负责对话生成（Gemini Pro/Flash 可以接入这里）\n- **Embedding 模型** — 负责向量转换（OpenViking 记忆召回用）\n\nOpenViking 的 embedding 是根据配置的 provider 来的，跟 product-selector 用什么 chat 模型是两套独立的配置。\n\n**所以：**\n1. ✅ 我可以把 Gemini 加到 product-selector 的 models.json，让选品 agent 用 Gemini 跑对话\n2. ❓ 但 embedding 那边能不能用 Gemini，取决于 OpenViking 是否支持 Gemini embedding provider\n\n你先把 **Gemini API Key** 给我，我帮你加进去，同时帮你确认 OpenViking 那边 embedding 的配置能不能切换到 Gemini。\n\n你的 Gemini API Key 是哪个？我直接写到配置里。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30255,"output":667,"cacheRead":12745,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43667,"cost":{"input":0.0090765,"output":0.0008003999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0007646999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0106416}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775644656406,"responseId":"062562f064463557d6ca58d72601a183"}}
