{"type":"message","id":"c92bf64f","parentId":"86e23047","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:39:04.548Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-08 18:37:59 GMT+8] Feishu[kiit] DM | ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb [msg:om_x100b5256b2f49058c365a971d0c6675]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5256b2f49058c365a971d0c6675\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-04-08 18:36 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n}\n```\n\nEmbedding  这个很费吗"}],"timestamp":1775644744542}}
{"type":"message","id":"d114440f","parentId":"c92bf64f","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:39:29.351Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if embedding is expensive. Let me think about this.\n\nEmbedding costs are generally quite low compared to LLM generation costs. Embedding models are usually much smaller and faster. \n\nFor context:\n- MiniMax's embedding API pricing is typically very cheap - around $0.1-0.5 per million tokens\n- A typical conversation message might be a few hundred tokens to embed\n- Even with thousands of messages stored, the embedding storage and computation costs are minimal\n\nThe \"insufficient balance\" error likely happened because:\n1. The user's MiniMax developer account had a very small amount of free credits or a low free tier\n2. Or they've been running many embedding requests\n\nLet me estimate:\n\n\nA single message around 500 tokens would cost roughly $0.0001 to embed at typical MiniMax pricing, so even 10,000 messages would only be about $1. If the user has exhausted their balance, it's likely due to either a very limited free credit allocation or an unusually high volume of requests rather than the cost being inherently high.\n\nLooking at the actual error from the logs, OpenViking attempted an embedding call to MiniMax and received an \"insufficient balance\" response, which suggests their API key has no remaining credits rather than the pricing being prohibitive. Let me break down the actual costs—embedding at roughly $0.1-0.3 per million tokens is extremely economical, so the real question is how many tokens they're actually processing and what their plan includes.\n\nIf MiniMax's free tier only gave them a few dollars of credits and they've been running embeddings on thousands of messages across multiple conversations, that could easily deplete it. I should clarify whether they're on a paid plan or using the free allocation, since the math on usage volume matters here.","thinkingSignature":"f02ac37497ccba17ef6c4311325a24c651198718e4971f9527915c6dc2a4eb66"},{"type":"text","text":"不贵，embedding 是最便宜的 AI API 之一。\n\n**参考价格（一般行情）：**\n- Embedding：约 **$0.1~0.5 / 百万 tokens**\n- 主模型对话：约 **$2~10 / 百万 tokens**\n\n差距几十倍。embedding 就是把文字转成数字向量，快且便宜。\n\n**你当时收到 insufficient balance**，更可能是：\n- MiniMax 开发者账户的**赠送金用完了**（新用户有一点免费额度）\n- 不是因为消费很高，而是账户清零了\n\n我估计你这段时间对话的 embedding 消耗，大概也就几分钱到几毛钱的人民币，不会是几十块那种级别。\n\n你去 MiniMax 控制台看一下账户余额，确认一下是不是真的归零了。如果还有几块钱余额，应该够用很久。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35,"output":528,"cacheRead":39053,"cacheWrite":4034,"totalTokens":43650,"cost":{"input":0.0000105,"output":0.0006336,"cacheRead":0.00234318,"cacheWrite":0.00151275,"total":0.0045000299999999995}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775644744548,"responseId":"06256348eea0d1e173c3f045972bb56e"}}
