{"type":"message","id":"9a3a1f10","parentId":"0181983b","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:46:18.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"400 means the server responded, so the endpoint is reachable. 400 is a \"Bad Request\" error, which makes sense because the request format or parameters might not be correct. But the important thing is the network is fine - the API is reachable.\n\nThe issue is likely that the `google-ai` API type in models.json isn't a valid type that OpenClaw supports. OpenClaw primarily supports `openai-completions` and `anthropic-messages` API types.\n\nLet me think about this - for Gemini via Google AI, the API endpoint and format are different from OpenAI. OpenClaw might not natively support the `google-ai` API type in models.json.\n\n\nI should switch to using OpenRouter as an intermediary for Gemini instead, since OpenRouter handles the `google/gemini-2.0-flash` model and uses the standard OpenAI-compatible format that OpenClaw can work with. This way I can route through OpenRouter rather than trying to use Google's API directly.","thinkingSignature":"945bedaef99edb41ff9e9a23ef31d29c589bde6928e32700cb342ef858e6f504"},{"type":"text","text":"网络通（返回 400），说明能连上 Google API。问题出在 **API 类型不匹配** —— OpenClaw 的 models.json 不认 `google-ai` 这个 API 类型。\n\n切到 OpenRouter 方案，OpenRouter 支持 Gemini，格式是标准 OpenAI：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8mis1tz6vpbt_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/product-selector/models.json","content":"{\n  \"providers\": {\n    \"openrouter\": {\n      \"baseUrl\": \"https://openrouter.ai/api/v1\",\n      \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n      \"models\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"auto\",\n          \"name\": \"OpenRouter Auto\",\n          \"reasoning\": false,\n          \"input\": [\n            \"text\",\n            \"image\"\n          ],\n          \"cost\": {\n            \"input\": 0,\n            \"output\": 0,\n            \"cacheRead