{"type":"message","id":"5d728dfb","parentId":"72721a37","timestamp":"2026-04-08T10:46:33.820Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but the API key I used for OpenRouter is the existing one. The user's Google API key (AIzaSyDLi65k75qE_76nMM-i2aPhzHLUmKKZK7Y) was for direct Google AI, not OpenRouter. OpenRouter needs its own API key.\n\nActually, looking at the original models.json, the OpenRouter API key was already configured. But for Gemini via OpenRouter, the user would need an OpenRouter API key. Let me check - does the user have an OpenRouter key with Gemini access?\n\nActually, the OpenRouter API key `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` is already in the config - but I don't know if it's valid or has credits.\n\n\nI'm realizing there's a fundamental mismatch here - the Google API key the user provided won't work with OpenRouter, which needs its own separate API key. Since OpenRouter routes to various providers including Google models, I'd need to verify whether the existing OpenRouter key can actually access Google's Gemini models or if the user needs to set up a different configuration. So the user provided their Google AI API key, but if OpenRouter is going to route to Google's Gemini models, the API key needs to belong to OpenRouter instead. I should ask whether they have an OpenRouter account and its API key, or if they'd prefer to try the direct Google AI approach instead—though that would require figuring out why the `google-ai` API type might not be working in OpenClaw.","thinkingSignature":"435f2c954efd3d5c8aea5e7f879271ed0334e6e18eb111c350ccee344818c845"},{"type":"text","text":"等等，发现问题：\n\nOpenRouter 方案需要 **OpenRouter 的 API Key**（路由到 Gemini），但配置里填的是 OpenRouter 现有的 key，不确定是否有额度。\n\n而你刚给的 `AIzaSyDLi...` 是 **Google AI 原生 key**，只能直连 Google，不能用于 OpenRouter。\n\n两个方案哪个你有资源：\n\n**方案 A：直连 Google AI（你给的 key）**\n- 需要搞清楚 OpenClaw 为何不认 `google-ai` API 类型\n- 我查一下 OpenClaw 支持的原生 API 类型列表